OL,3,CWhy the number of MPs in Wales is
OL,4,Cbeing cut from 40 to 32
OL,6,FThese changes came into effect after a
OL,7,Fboundary commission review that ended
OL,8,Flast year.
OL,10,FIt all follows an earlier UK
OL,11,FGovernment decision to ensure each
OL,12,Fconstituency has a similar number of
OL,13,Fvoters in it - between 69,724 and
OL,14,F77,062.
OL,16,FBecause of that, Wales will lose eight
OL,17,Fseats, as the country has some of the
OL,18,Fsmallest constituencies in the UK.
OL,20,FReviews have taken place in each of
OL,21,Fthe four nations.
