OL,3,CWhy the number of MPs in Wales is
OL,4,Cbeing cut from 40 to 32
OL,6,FThe boundaries of nearly all existing
OL,7,FWelsh constituencies have been
OL,8,Faltered, with the exception of Ynys
OL,9,FMon, which has "protected status" and
OL,10,Fwill have no changes to the island of
OL,11,FAnglesey seat's name or boundaries.
OL,13,FEssentially, it means the areas MPs
OL,14,Fwill be representing is changing in
OL,15,Fmany cases.
OL,17,FVoters will have to find the name of
OL,18,Ftheir constituency that has changed
OL,19,Fsince the 2019 General Election when
OL,20,Fthey choose a candidate to be their MP
OL,21,Ffrom 4 July.
