OL,3,CWhy the number of MPs in Wales is
OL,4,Cbeing cut from 40 to 32
OL,6,FWith boundary changes affecting most
OL,7,Fconstituencies, many voters will be
OL,8,Fvoting in unfamiliar territory.
OL,10,FElections to the Welsh Parliament are
OL,11,Fcontrolled by the Senedd, not the UK
OL,12,FParliament and the rules for the way
OL,13,Fthey are run are due to change.
OL,15,FFrom 2026, there will be more Senedd
OL,16,Fmembers - 96, compared to the current
OL,17,F60 - and the way they will be elected
OL,18,Fis changing too, from a mixture of
OL,19,Ffirst-past-the-post and proportional
OL,20,Frepresentation to a fully proportional
OL,21,Fsystem.
